You really only need one or the other depending on the style of the code you are using in the rest of your project.<p>If you write js using semi-colons everywhere:<p><pre><code>    (function () { })(this);

    (function () { })(this);

    (function () { })(this);
</code></pre>
If you dont want to use semi-colons unless you have to:<p><pre><code>    ;(function () { })(this)

    ;(function () { })(this)

    ;(function () { })(this)
</code></pre>
Basically, never start lines with `(` or `[` without semis and don't throw in line breaks liberally without understanding what semicolon insertion is going to happen.<p><a href="http://blog.izs.me/post/2353458699/an-open-letter-to-javascript-leaders-regarding" rel="nofollow">http://blog.izs.me/post/2353458699/an-open-letter-to-javascr...</a>
